
# LeetCode POTD - 1st April 2026

## Problem
Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array

## Difficulty
Easy

## Approach
Use two pointers:
- `i` keeps track of the last unique element
- `j` scans the array
- If nums[j] != nums[i], move i and place nums[j]

## Code
```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int removeDuplicates(vector<int>& nums) {
        int i = 0;

        for (int j = 1; j < nums.size(); j++) {
            if (nums[j] != nums[i]) {
                i++;
                nums[i] = nums[j];
            }
        }

        return i + 1;
    }
};
